      <accessrestrict id="aspace_0e194cb88587702446aa4f1efc6360ac">
         <head>Information about Access</head>
         <p>This material is open for research.</p>
         <p>6 (Roll) (drawings): Restricted fragile material. Reference copies may be requested. For further information consult the appropriate curator.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <acqinfo id="aspace_de67028503b3d4250402a403e28f4b92">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition note</head>
         <p>Gift of A. B. Chapman, 1898.</p>  
      </acqinfo>
      <arrangement id="aspace_3360a6b0ad5602fa2ac9ba1ed122643e">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Organized into two series: I. Music, 1874-1897. II. Drawings, undated.</p>  
      </arrangement>
      <bioghist id="aspace_d1df0e0cb1dd3207fda3ae0152294243">
         <head>A. B. (Aaron Bennet) Chapman</head>
         <p>A. B. (Aaron Bennet) Chapman attended Yale College, leaving in 1871, his junior year, due to health problems. He lived in New Haven, Connecticut, during the 1860s-1890s.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <prefercite id="aspace_f4e5b17855a5e9ca0ab710652cfbe22a">
         <head>Cite As</head>
         <p>A. B. Chapman Music and Drawings. General Collection, Beinecke Rare Book and Manuscript Library, Yale University.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <processinfo id="aspace_d7411671b631a765fccbf4189f868166">
         <head>Processing Notes</head>
         <p>This collection consists of materials formerly classed as MS Vault Shelves +Chapman. In 2013, the collection received a baseline level of processing, including rehousing and minimal organization. Folder titles are based on information provided by the donor or adapted from card catalog descriptions. Contents of 6 (Roll) were not verified due to fragile condition. An accompanying "letter from Chapman to Professor Van Name, about the collection and other manuscripts given to YUL, undated," was noted in the card catalog, but was not found at the time of processing.</p>  
      </processinfo>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_37d65674e86690e070a347060c98124d">
         <head>Description of the Papers</head>
         <p>Autograph manuscript music, including symphonies and hymns, scores; arrangements of hymns and other choral music, scores and parts; a passion-play, score, with watercolor drawings of curtain and stage designs; and notebooks containing music sketches and related notes about music and Christianity. An oversize rolled sheet contains unidentified ink and watercolor drawings.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <userestrict id="aspace_e6ac470e247d6e96715e9dd83a814908">
         <head>Ownership  Copyright</head>
         <p>The A. B. Chapman Music and Drawings is the physical property of the Beinecke Rare Book and Manuscript Library, Yale University. Literary rights, including copyright, belong to the authors or their legal heirs and assigns. For further information, consult the appropriate curator.</p>  
      </userestrict>
